extendedInfo.description: Energy Saving Trust estimates that you could save up to 2 monthâs worth of fuel yearly by driving efficiently. Use the FuelGood app to track your fuel efficiency and the potential savings you could make by using our fuel-efficient driving tips.The FuelGood app allows you to choose your car type, car age and engine size. It tracks your journeys and gives you an estimate of the savings you make if you are driving efficiently. FuelGood uses GPS to track your position along your journey and calculates an estimated saving on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions for your car against the average values for a driver in your car category.Within the Journey List section of the app, you can select different journeys to compare your savings over similar distances and to see how you are progressing.There is also a Tips section for help on improving your fuel-efficient driving.

reviews.title: nice peice of kit
reviews.comment: just running this ap made me a lot more aware of how i was driving and had a very positive effect. Although the savings to me are not massive day to day they will be considerable over time.
reviews.author: Nik Wilson

reviews.title: Poor show
reviews.comment: It starts fine but as soon as my phone locks the app has to restart! Otherwise could be a useful app otherwise. So for it to work I would have to keep checking the phone while driving. I should be able to start it and put the phone down until the end of my journey.
reviews.author: Robert Kemp

reviews.title: Crashes Alot!
reviews.comment: Good when it worked, but now it doesn\'t even load up and just stays the opening screen.
reviews.author: Andrew Donnachie

reviews.title: I like the idea.... But.....
reviews.comment: How can this be app accurate? It doesn\'t know what gear I\'m in, whether it\'s manual or auto. The condition of the engine. It could ask for the last MOT figures for emissions. I could be doing 50mph in 4th,5th or 6th gear. Sorry but it needs more details than type of fuel, size of car and age of car to be any where near accurate enough to predict fuel saving...... Just glad it was a free app. But on the positive side, I do like the idea behind it.
reviews.author: Brett Appleton

reviews.title: Does not work
reviews.comment: Useless app will not open at all. Have tried reinstalling several time but still will not open. So should be zero stars!!!
reviews.author: Fiona Burton

reviews.title: Not impressed
reviews.comment: By it\'s very nature it does not allow for driving style, so tells me to do what I\'ve been doing all my life. Might be useful for some people who need better driving skills. Uninstalled.
reviews.author: Lynda Hill
